der less favourable but more probable scenarios. Our findings suggest that, unless bold steps are taken to improve management, then a great deal of money would have been, and will continue to be, wasted. The essential element of an improved management approach would be to practice conservation triage, focusing effort only on priority areas and species, and accepting trade-offs between conserving biodiversity and reducing invasions. {\u00a9} 2016 Elsevier Ltd", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "van Wilgen, Brian W.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fill, Jennifer M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Baard, Johan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cheney, Chad", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Forsyth, Aurelia T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kraaij, Tineke", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 2", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/aa8fd0e24599c8058ecb05a05a4f728c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/33df93e4fbaa7b6c54dcd4c3a7b3579ef3fd2268a66e5142894a6572daba1226", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/8VH6TNYW", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/8VH6TNYW", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6f5ffc7849d46604da7c0a2a9ff5033c!/b12515-15003", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.biocon.2016.06.008", "relation": "isVariantFormOf", "resource_type": "publication", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.7430682", "relation": "isCitedBy", "resource_type": "publication-report", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation"